  "interpretation": [
    "METHODOLOGICAL NOTE: Rank normalization maps ANY distribution to ~Uniform[0,1], so rank-KS differences are trivially small and uninformative. The LOG-TRANSFORMED KS and GAP STATISTICS are the real tests.",
    "LOG-KS: PDG masses nearest to OEIS_terms (D=0.7575), all others: knot_determinants=0.9478, EC_conductors=0.9819",
    "ALL pairwise log-KS tests are highly significant (p < 1e-10): these four domains have genuinely DIFFERENT distribution shapes. No cross-domain distributional universality detected.",
    "GAP STATISTICS: PDG masses nearest to knot_determinants (Euclidean distance in [std/mean, skew, kurtosis] space = 10.7512)",
    "BOTTOM LINE: PDG masses and knot determinants share the most similar gap structure (nearest-neighbor spacing), but all four domains have completely different log-scale distribution shapes. The shared gap structure likely reflects both being small-N heavy-tailed sequences rather than a deep cross-domain connection."
